 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-STEER: Hypothesis prompt compilation — temperature-calibrated steering vectors. CONTEXT: Current FEGH outputs 'What connects session-X to session-Y?' — a null steering vector that activates nothing in the LLM latent space. RATIONALE: Hypothesis phrasing IS latent space navigation. The quality of the steering vector determines convergence speed. INV-CONVERGENCE-006. APPROACH: (1) Add compile_hypothesis_prompt(source_obs, target_obs, temperature, grounding) -> String to routing.rs. (2) ObservationSummary: entity, body_text (first 200 chars of :exploration/body), keywords (tokenized), file_paths (extracted from text via regex for path-like strings). GroundingContext: relevant_files (Vec<String>), spec_ids (Vec<String>), function_names (Vec<String>), line_ranges (Vec<(String, usize, usize)>). (3) Temperature regimes: HIGH (T>0.8): 'What is the relationship between {summarize_cluster(source, 30)} and {summarize_cluster(target, 30)}?'. MEDIUM (0.4<T<=0.8): 'Your observations about {source_summary} and {target_summary} both reference {shared_keywords}. How are they connected? Check {relevant_files}.'. LOW (T<=0.4): 'Does {grounding.specific_mechanism} in {source_file} affect {target_property} as described in {spec_id}? Check lines {start}-{end} for {expected_pattern}.'. (4) Shared keyword extraction: intersection of source and target keyword sets, minus stopwords. (5) File path extraction: regex for patterns like path/to/file.ext:LNN in observation text. (6) Hole-type phrasing: beta0 bridge = 'How does X relate to Y?', beta1 falsification = 'X explains Y explains X — what EXTERNAL evidence confirms this?', beta2 void = 'You mapped the boundary of Z — what is inside?'. (7) Tag each compiled hypothesis with its PhrasingPattern for CE-META calibration. ACCEPTANCE: (A) At T=0.1 on Go CLI with grounding: hypothesis contains file path and spec ID. (B) At T=0.9 on empty store: hypothesis is broad and open-ended. (C) Shared keywords appear in medium-T hypotheses. (D) Hole type determines phrasing structure. (E) Every hypothesis tagged with PhrasingPattern. (F) No hypothesis contains raw EntityId hex (all resolved to text). DEPENDS-ON: CE-TEMP (temperature-adaptive FEGH provides bridges), CE-CONN (provides observation summaries). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/routing.rs (compile_hypothesis_prompt + ObservationSummary + GroundingContext)"
